"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143120","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-09-05","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2019-09-05T10:33:24.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143120/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143120/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143120/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-09-02","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants have died in the last 12 months after having been assessed by her Department as fit for work.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","284785"
