"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143216","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-05","<p>​We have maintained regular discussions with key actors on Venezuela following British recognition of Juan Guaido as interim Venezuelan President. Through our Ambassador and internationally, we are working closely with like-minded partners to achieve a peaceful resolution to the current crisis and a return to democracy and unimpeded access for humanitarian aid.</p><p>We hope that this, along with sanctions regimes imposed by the EU, the US and Canada, will encourage Nicolas Maduro to re-enter Norwegian-brokered negotiations with the Opposition in good faith.</p>","Tamworth","Christopher Pincher",,"2019-09-05T16:17:38.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143216/answer","Biography information for Christopher Pincher","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143216/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Venezuela: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the Venezuelan’s Government’s withdrawal from negotiations with the opposition.","false","Biography information for Andrea Jenkyns","Morley and Outwood","Andrea Jenkyns","284884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143217","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-05","<p>We are disappointed that North Korea has conducted multiple short-range ballistic missile tests in recent weeks. These are a violation of UN Security Council Resolutions. The British Government has repeatedly expressed its concern at North Korea’s breaches of international law and has ensured UN Security Council consideration of the matter, most recently on Tuesday 27 August. We urge North Korea to cease these tests and re-engage in talks with the United States. Until the dismantlement of North Korea’s nuclear and missile programmes, UN sanctions must remain and be fully enforced. It is our firm belief that complete, verifiable and irreversible denuclearisation is the path to a peaceful and more prosperous future for the North Korean people.</p><p>​</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-09-05T14:51:48.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143217/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143217/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","North Korea: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the recent missile tests in North Korea.","false","Biography information for Andrea Jenkyns","Morley and Outwood","Andrea Jenkyns","284887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143218","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Digital Discharge Bag project is currently being supported by the Department through the local Academic Health Science Networks (AHSNs). The AHSNs integrate the work of academia, industry and the National Health Service to accelerate the development, adoption and spread of innovative ideas and technologies across the system. If the product proves its clinical and cost effectiveness, we would expect to see it widely adopted across the system - in line with the Accelerated Access Collaborative’s aim to make the best treatments and technologies available to patients regardless of where they live.</p>","Mid Bedfordshire","Ms Nadine Dorries",,"2019-09-09T17:29:01.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143218/answer","Biography information for Ms Nadine Dorries","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143218/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143218/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-02","Telemedicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if his Department will extend the NHS’ post-hospital discharge digital bag project to other areas in England beyond Lancashire and South Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Andrea Jenkyns","Morley and Outwood","Andrea Jenkyns","284486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143219","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>We have established a new unit – NHSX – to drive forward the digital transformation of health and social care, and give patients the tools to access online information and services safely and effectively.</p><p>We are providing a coreset of national digital services for people to transact with the health and care system and find information.</p><p>Innovators can build onto these services for a consistent, trusted and joined up digital experience.</p><p>NHSX will also define and mandate technology and design standards for digital services used within the NHS and social care, ensuring all publicly-funded source code is open by default.</p>","Mid Bedfordshire","Ms Nadine Dorries",,"2019-09-09T18:13:36.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143219/answer","Biography information for Ms Nadine Dorries","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143219/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143219/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-02","Telemedicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to improve the (a) range and (b) quality of digital NHS healthcare services offered to patients.","false","Biography information for Andrea Jenkyns","Morley and Outwood","Andrea Jenkyns","284708"
