"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143421","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) were created in April 2013, therefore information is not available prior to that date. Each London CCG is named after the borough it serves. London CCG allocations for 2013/14 onwards are shown in the attached table, including the proportion of the total London allocation that this equates to.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-09-09T14:54:40.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143421/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143421/answer","190905 - PQ284916 - London CCG Allocations 2013 onwards - FINAL.xlsx","PQ284916 London CCG Allocations 2013 onwards","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143421/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-02","Health Services: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the proportion of funding allocated to each Care Commissioning Groups in each borough of London in each of the last ten years.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","284916"
