"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143437","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Defence Infrastructure Organisation and its Industry Partner undertake routine internal audits of its Environmental Management Systems delivered across the UK Training Estate which includes Cape Wrath.</p><p>No additional audits are planned to be completed this year that specifically investigate the environmental impacts of military activity on Cape Wrath.</p><p>It is not routine for the Ministry of Defence to externally publish these internal environmental audits.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan",,"2019-09-09T15:12:14.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143437/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143437/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143437/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-02","Cape Wrath","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if his Department will publish any environmental audit it has carried out on its activities on Cape Wrath.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","285057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143439","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department will continue to work closely with other Departments to implement the Government’s policy on access to cannabis-based products for medicinal use; to work with researchers, the industry and others to improve the evidence base for these products; to ensure product availability; and to provide clinicians with guidance on prescribing these products where clinically appropriate.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-09-09T15:22:26.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143439/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143439/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-02","Cannabis: Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if his Department will produce a cross-government plan for the issuing of medicinal cannabis under prescription by the end of 2019.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","284922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143440","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-09-09T16:26:34.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143440/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143440/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Saudi Arabia: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Saudi Arabian counterpart on the protection of (a) the LGBT community and (b) religious minorities in Saudi Arabia.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","284926"
