"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143476","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","<p>This question on ministerial travel can only be obtainable at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>However, the Government publishes data on ministerial overseas travel on a quarterly basis in arrears on GOV.UK. Information on costs on overseas travel from July to September 2019 is expected to be published in December 2019.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers must ensure that they always make efficient and cost-effective travel arrangements, and normal practice is for Ministers to travel by standard class.</p>","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","285117","2019-09-09T13:01:54.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143476/answer","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143476/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143476/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-02","Treasury: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) first class, (b) second class and (c) in total in 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","285152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143478","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-09-09","<p>In the 2018 calendar year, the ministers’ private offices spend on air and rail travel was:</p><p>Air (standard/economy class) – £12,935.60</p><p>Air (business/first class) – £4005.60</p><p>Rail (standard class) – £16,730.70</p><p>Rail (first class) – None</p><p> </p><p>Total - £33,671.90</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-09-09T14:11:13.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143478/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143478/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143478/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-09-02","Ministry of Justice: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) first class, (b) second class and (c) in total in 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","285157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143479","Scotland Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Scotland spend on ministerial travel by (a) first class, (b) second class and (c) in the financial year 2018-19 is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>First Class</strong></p></td><td><p>£ 214</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Second Class</strong></p></td><td><p>£ 105,625</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p>£ 105,839</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack",,"2019-09-09T16:59:08.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143479/answer","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143479/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143479/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-09-02","Scotland Office: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) first class, (b) second class and (c) in total in 2018.","false","Biography information for Ruth Jones","Newport West","Ruth Jones","285160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143480","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-05","<p>​Chapter VI of the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea Arbitral Tribunal Award (18 March 2015) considers this issue in detail and makes the relevant conclusions in paragraph 428.</p>","Tamworth","Christopher Pincher",,"2019-09-05T16:15:20.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143480/answer","Biography information for Christopher Pincher","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143480/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143480/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","British Indian Ocean Territory: Sovereignty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 23 July 2019 to Question 277209, which paragraphs in Chapter VI of the Award of the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea Tribunal of March 2015 conclude that the 1965 Agreement to the detachment of the Chagos Archipelago was legally binding upon both Mauritius and the United Kingdom.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","285310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143481","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-05","<p>Section 4 of the Ministerial and other Pensions and Salaries Act 1991 sets out Ministers' entitlement to severance payments. Any such payments are published in each department's audited annual accounts, and these accounts can be found in the Ministry of Defence Annual Report and Account Index where the severance pay for the right hon. Member for South Staffordshire will be published in 2020. As detailed in Section 4 of the Ministerial and other Pensions and Salaries Act 1991:</p><p>'the amount of the payment to which a person who has ceased to hold a relevant office is entitled under this section is an amount equal to one-quarter of the annual amount of the salary which was being paid to that person in respect of that office immediately before the material time.'</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2019-09-05T15:19:46.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143481/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143481/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143481/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-02","Former Ministers: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what severance payment the rt hon. Member for South Staffordshire received after he left his position as Secretary of State for Defence.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","285450"
