"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143483","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-05","<p>​The Foreign Secretary raised the situation in Hong Kong with Chinese State Councillor Wang Yi on 31 July, during which he discussed the importance of upholding the 'One Country, Two Systems' framework.</p><p>In respect of British Nationals, we keep travel advice under constant review to ensure it reflects our assessment of risk to British nationals and includes information on the most relevant issues for British nationals travelling or living abroad. We encourage British people to read our travel advice to help them make informed decisions.</p><p>In respect of BN(O)s, we maintain that the best solution for all the people of Hong Kong, including the BN(O) passport holders that live there, is full respect for the rights and freedoms guaranteed in the Joint Declaration.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-09-05T14:03:13.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143483/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143483/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143483/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Hong Kong: Civil Disorder","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Chinese counterpart on behalf of (a) British subjects and (b) people with joint British-Chinese nationality on protecting them from the civil unrest in Hong Kong.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","285176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143484","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-09-09","<p>Consistent with the requirement of the Act that the Code of Practice be developed in consultation with stakeholders, we are currently considering the format for stakeholder engagement and will make an announcement in due course. We are also committed to carrying out a public consultation on the draft Code of Practice as part of the development process, allowing all interested parties to directly respond to the proposals.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","284279","2019-09-09T15:28:33.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143484/answer","Biography information for Luke Hall","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143484/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143484/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-09-02","Parking: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 27 June 2019 to Question 266812 on Parking (Code of Practice) Act 2019, what opportunities for public consultation there will be as part of the development of the code of practice.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","285286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143485","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Government is committed to reforming the leasehold market so that it is fairer for consumers. This includes banning new leasehold houses, unless there are exceptional circumstances, and reducing ground rents for both houses and flats to zero</p><p><br> We will also give freeholders on private and mixed-tenure estates the right to challenge the reasonableness of these charges and the ability to apply to the First-tier Tribunal to appoint a new property manager</p><p><br> The Government will bring forward the legislation to implement these changes as soon as parliamentary time allows.</p>","Tatton","Esther McVey",,"2019-09-09T15:20:25.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143485/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143485/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-09-02","Leasehold: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to implement the leasehold reforms referred to by the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government in her oral contribution of 11 July 2019, Official report, column 552.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","285397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143486","Cabinet Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>I refer the Honourable Gentleman to the answer given to PQ 279360 on 23 July.</p><p>The Cabinet Office is currently investigating various financial wellbeing options and will<br>determine our approach next year, once this work has been completed.</p>","Torbay","Kevin Foster",,"2019-09-09T10:27:26.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143486/answer","Biography information for Kevin Foster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143486/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143486/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-09-02","Cabinet Office: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 23 July 2019 to Question 279360 on Cabinet Office: Credit Unions, what further steps he has taken to offer a payroll deduction service to enable employees to join a credit union; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","285170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143487","Department for Education","false","2019-09-06","<p>The 30 hours childcare schemes are a devolved matter and the Department for Education has a remit for the 30 hours entitlement for England. Questions about schemes in Scotland and Wales should be referred to the devolved administrations.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284288 ; 284292 ; 284294 ; 284406 ; 285419","2019-09-06T17:40:13.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143487/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143487/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143487/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the cost to the public purse was of the 30 hour free childcare scheme in Scotland in the 2018-19 financial year.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","285418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143488","Department for Education","false","2019-09-06","<p>The 30 hours childcare schemes are a devolved matter and the Department for Education has a remit for the 30 hours entitlement for England. Questions about schemes in Scotland and Wales should be referred to the devolved administrations.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284288 ; 284292 ; 284294 ; 284406 ; 285418","2019-09-06T17:40:13.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143488/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143488/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the cost to the public purse was of the 30 hour free childcare scheme in Scotland in the 2017-18 financial year.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","285419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143489","Department for Education","false","2019-09-09","<p>We want parents to have access to a range of affordable childcare, giving them increased flexibility in their working hours and helping children thrive in the crucial early years. That is why the department is investing £3.5 billion in our early education offers this year alone. The cost of 30 hours free childcare is set in table 1, attached. The total for 2017-18 is due to rounding.</p><p>The number of children that have benefitted from 30 hours free childcare in each year is set out in table 2, attached.</p><p>In total, around 600,000 children aged 3 and 4 years old benefitted from a 30 hours place throughout the first 2 years of delivery.</p><p>We do not hold data on estimates of the number of parents that have benefitted from the 30 hours entitlement in England.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284299 ; 284395 ; 284402 ; 285422","2019-09-09T14:23:32.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143489/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143489/answer","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_30_hours_childcare.xls","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143489/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the cost to the public purse was of the 30 hour free childcare scheme in England in the 2017-18 financial year.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","285420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143490","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","This information is not available since hours of childcare used is not collected as part of the Tax-free Childcare application process.","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2019-09-09T09:51:27.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143490/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143490/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many hours of childcare recipients of tax free childcare apply for by the proportion of applicants that apply for those hours.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","285421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143491","Department for Education","false","2019-09-09","<p>We want parents to have access to a range of affordable childcare, giving them increased flexibility in their working hours and helping children thrive in the crucial early years. That is why the department is investing £3.5 billion in our early education offers this year alone. The cost of 30 hours free childcare is set in table 1, attached. The total for 2017-18 is due to rounding.</p><p>The number of children that have benefitted from 30 hours free childcare in each year is set out in table 2, attached.</p><p>In total, around 600,000 children aged 3 and 4 years old benefitted from a 30 hours place throughout the first 2 years of delivery.</p><p>We do not hold data on estimates of the number of parents that have benefitted from the 30 hours entitlement in England.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284299 ; 284395 ; 284402 ; 285420","2019-09-09T14:23:32.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143491/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143491/answer","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_30_hours_childcare.xls","284299_284395_284402_285420_285422_table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143491/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children use the 30 hours free childcare scheme.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","285422"
