"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143533","Department for Education","false","2019-09-05","<p>The amount of funds expiring in employers’ digital apprenticeship service accounts in July 2019 was £44 million, and in August 2019 it was £52 million.</p><p>As well as funding apprenticeships in levy-paying employers, levy contributions are also used to fund training for existing apprenticeship learners and new apprenticeships in employers that do not pay the levy. We do not anticipate that all employers who pay the levy will need or want to use all the funds in their accounts, though they are able to do this if they wish.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch","284461","2019-09-05T15:54:03.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143533/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143533/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143533/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-09-02","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the value of apprenticeship levy funds expiring from employers' accounts was in July 2019; and what plans the Government has for those funds.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","285272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143534","Department for International Development","false","2019-09-09","<p>The UK works closely with the Global Polio Eradication Initiative (GPEI) to support their efforts in promoting and delivering polio vaccination programmes in Afghanistan, Pakistan and Nigeria. We follow developments closely in country through DFID country office staff and through our engagement with GPEI headquarters in Geneva. The successes of the GPEI in Nigeria is evidenced by that country’s achievement of three years without wild polio virus.</p><p> </p><p>During engagement with the GPEI and during bilaterals with the remaining endemic countries the UK stresses the importance of understanding the context-specific blocks to eradication and promoting the great value of immunisation.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-09-09T16:55:54.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143534/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143534/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143534/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-02","Poliomyelitis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps his Department is taking to support the promotion of polio immunisation in (a) Pakistan, (b) Afghanistan and (c) Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","284939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143535","Department for International Development","false","2019-09-09","<p>The UK is a leading supporter of the Global Polio Eradication Initiative (GPEI) which is responsible for polio programme delivery. Working with state and local governments, GPEI provides additional training and safety measure to protect health workers working in high risk and volatile settings. As part of our risk management, the UK closely monitors GPEI to ensure prevention, reporting and mitigation measures are in place.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-09-09T16:56:14.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143535/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143535/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143535/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-02","Poliomyelitis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps the UK Government is taking to support and protect health workers so that they are able to continue to provide polio immunisation programmes under the Global Polio Eradication Initiative.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","285187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143536","Department for International Development","false","2019-09-09","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-09-09T16:58:59.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143536/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143536/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143536/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-02","Poliomyelitis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps his Department is taking to work alongside the One Last Push campaign to ensure that (a) funding and (b) other support is available for polio vaccination programmes in countries at risk from that disease.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","285188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143537","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-09-06","<p>The Personal Independence Payment assessment is not a medical assessment and there is no requirement for the Health Professional to diagnose a condition and recommend treatment options. Health Professionals are trained to be experts in disability analysis and to assess how a disability or syndrome affects the functional capability of each individual claimant. Whilst there is no specific training relating to post-polio syndrome, all Health Professionals have access to a range of resources, including relevant training on specific impairments, including those that are mental, intellectual and cognitive, as well as experienced clinicians to support them in assessing claimants with conditions that they may not be familiar with.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","284945","2019-09-06T11:05:40.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143537/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143537/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143537/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-09-02","Personal Independence Payment: Post-polio Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether personal independence payment assessors receive training on the symptoms of post-polio syndrome so that they are able to identify the complex symptoms experienced by claimants with that syndrome.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","285189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143538","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-09-06","<p>The Personal Independence Payment assessment is not a medical assessment and there is no requirement for the Health Professional to diagnose a condition and recommend treatment options. Health Professionals are trained to be experts in disability analysis and to assess how a disability or syndrome affects the functional capability of each individual claimant. Whilst there is no specific training relating to post-polio syndrome, all Health Professionals have access to a range of resources, including relevant training on specific impairments, including those that are mental, intellectual and cognitive, as well as experienced clinicians to support them in assessing claimants with conditions that they may not be familiar with.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","285189","2019-09-06T11:05:40.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143538/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143538/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143538/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-09-02","Personal Independence Payment: Post-polio Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether personal independence payment assessments are adjusted to take account of the symptoms experienced by claimants diagnosed with post-polio syndrome.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","284945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143539","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>The UK Green Finance Strategy, launched on 2 July 2019, included a commitment to align Official Development Assistance (ODA) spending with the Paris Agreement on climate change.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-09-09T15:08:35.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143539/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143539/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143539/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Fossil Fuels: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make it his policy to prevent fossil fuel projects from being funded through his Department's foreign aid programmes.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","285448"
